ded readability the GlowLight device delivers.","fullscreen":true,"importSrc":"http://www.toptenreviews.com/i/rev/scrn/small/53374-nook-simple-touch3.jpg","src":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/AD3xCGssZUiMV59iVxTYCJ.jpg","credit":"","align":"","id":"AD3xCGssZUiMV59iVxTYCJ","mos":"https://dev.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/AD3xCGssZUiMV59iVxTYCJ.jpg","alt":""},"id":"f6e1602e-5474-469d-8c4d-90f743eee2f1","type":"image"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["The GlowLight NOOK also offers a 6-inch, anti-glare display and responsive touchscreen navigation. A power button located at the top of the chassis enables you to perform a hard reset if needed.","The only minor flaw this eBook reader possesses in terms of readability is its resolution, which is a bit lower than some competitors. The marginally low contrast makes the text appear slightly soft around the edges. However, the difference is minor and not likely something you’d notice unless you held the device side-by-side to an eReader with a higher resolution. The Nook Simple Touch GlowLight also does not offer a landscape mode, but at worst we chock this up to a trivial absence few people will miss."]},"id":"1bec65a3-4987-448c-b55b-ae7af5ced5b8","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Design &amp; Portability"},"id":"3033d522-3617-4a0b-84da-62e77446696b","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Beyond its adjustable reading light, one of the most appealing attributes of this digital reader is its design. Among dedicated eBook readers, the GlowLight NOOK rules in terms of ergonomics. The device has a soft-touch coating that gives the casing a smooth, rubberized feel and makes it comfortable to hold one-handed for extended periods of time. This is a notable departure from the hard, somewhat cheap-feeling plastic typical of most eReaders."]},"id":"30498dfa-c90c-4bdc-af2c-4c38736b705a","type":"text"},{"data":{"path":"/kUWMYPqTPCpaMfbvn32Pi3.jpg","link":{"href":"","rel":null,"target":""},"caption":"","fullscreen":true,"importSrc":"http://www.topte